#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an9.26"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.26:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.26:0.2"
msgid "3. Sattāvāsavagga "
msgstr "3. Abodes of Sentient Beings "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 26. Silāyūpasutta → silāyūpopamasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an9.26:0.3"
msgid "26. Silāyūpasutta "
msgstr "26. The Simile of the Stone Pillar "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.403, sc1
#. VAR: () → (evaṃ me sutaṃ) (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an9.26:1.1"
msgid "() "
msgstr "So I have heard. "

msgctxt "an9.26:1.2"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca sāriputto āyasmā ca candikāputto rājagahe viharanti veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: () → (āvuso …pe… etadavoca) (bj)
msgctxt "an9.26:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā candikāputto bhikkhū āmantesi (): "
msgstr "There Venerable Candikāputta addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "an9.26:1.4"
msgid "“devadatto, āvuso, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ deseti: "
msgstr "“Reverends, Devadatta teaches the mendicants like this: "

# NOTE: See BB’s note on variant readings. It seems to me that the distinction between cetasa and pannaya paricita is hinting at the distinction between ceto and pannavimutti.
msgctxt "an9.26:1.5"
msgid "‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā citaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ bhikkhuno kallaṃ veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr "‘When a mendicant’s mind is solidified by heart, it’s appropriate for them to say: "

# NOTE: Quadruple-nested close quotes!
msgctxt "an9.26:1.6"
msgid "khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāmī’”ti. "
msgstr "“I understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an9.26:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ candikāputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Sāriputta said to him, "

msgctxt "an9.26:2.2"
msgid "“na kho, āvuso candikāputta, devadatto bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ deseti: "
msgstr "“Reverend Candikāputta, Devadatta does not teach the mendicants like that. "

msgctxt "an9.26:2.3"
msgid "‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā citaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ bhikkhuno kallaṃ veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an9.26:2.4"
msgid "khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāmī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an9.26:2.5"
msgid "Evañca kho, āvuso, candikāputta, devadatto bhikkhūnaṃ dhammaṃ deseti: "
msgstr "He teaches like this: "

msgctxt "an9.26:2.6"
msgid "‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ bhikkhuno kallaṃ veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr "‘When a mendicant’s mind is well consolidated by heart, it’s appropriate for them to say: "

msgctxt "an9.26:2.7"
msgid "khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāmī’”ti. "
msgstr "“I understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
