msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.26:4.5"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ candikāputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "And for a third time, Sāriputta said to him, "

msgctxt "an9.26:4.6"
msgid "“na kho, āvuso candikāputta, devadatto bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ deseti: "
msgstr "“Reverend Candikāputta, Devadatta does not teach the mendicants like that. "

msgctxt "an9.26:4.7"
msgid "‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā citaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ bhikkhuno kallaṃ veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an9.26:4.8"
msgid "khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāmī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an9.26:4.9"
msgid "Evañca kho, āvuso candikāputta, devadatto bhikkhūnaṃ dhammaṃ deseti: "
msgstr "He teaches like this: "

msgctxt "an9.26:4.10"
msgid "‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ bhikkhuno kallaṃ veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr "‘When a mendicant’s mind is well consolidated by heart, it’s appropriate for them to say: "

msgctxt "an9.26:4.11"
msgid "khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāmī’ti. "
msgstr "“I understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.404, sc5
msgctxt "an9.26:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant’s mind well consolidated by heart? "

msgctxt "an9.26:5.2"
msgid "‘Vītarāgaṃ me cittan’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti; "
msgstr "The mind is well consolidated by heart when they know: ‘My mind is without greed.’ "

msgctxt "an9.26:5.3"
msgid "‘vītadosaṃ me cittan’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti; "
msgstr "… ‘My mind is without hate.’ "

msgctxt "an9.26:5.4"
msgid "‘vītamohaṃ me cittan’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti; "
msgstr "… ‘My mind is without delusion.’ "

msgctxt "an9.26:5.5"
msgid "‘asarāgadhammaṃ me cittan’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti; "
msgstr "… ‘My mind is not liable to become greedy.’ "

msgctxt "an9.26:5.6"
msgid "‘asadosadhammaṃ me cittan’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti; "
msgstr "… ‘My mind is not liable to become hateful.’ "

msgctxt "an9.26:5.7"
msgid "‘asamohadhammaṃ me cittan’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti; "
msgstr "… ‘My mind is not liable to become deluded.’ "

msgctxt "an9.26:5.8"
msgid "‘anāvattidhammaṃ me cittaṃ kāmabhavāyā’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti; "
msgstr "… ‘My mind is not liable to return to rebirth in the sensual realm.’ "

msgctxt "an9.26:5.9"
msgid "‘anāvattidhammaṃ me cittaṃ rūpabhavāyā’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti; "
msgstr "… ‘My mind is not liable to return to rebirth in the realm of luminous form.’ "

msgctxt "an9.26:5.10"
msgid "‘anāvattidhammaṃ me cittaṃ arūpabhavāyā’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "… ‘My mind is not liable to return to rebirth in the formless realm.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.26:5.11"
msgid "Evaṃ sammā vimuttacittassa kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno bhusā cepi cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā cakkhussa āpāthaṃ āgacchanti, nevassa cittaṃ pariyādiyanti; "
msgstr "When a mendicant’s mind is rightly freed like this, even if compelling sights come into the range of vision they don’t occupy their mind. "

msgctxt "an9.26:5.12"
msgid "amissīkatamevassa cittaṃ hoti ṭhitaṃ āneñjappattaṃ, vayaṃ cassānupassati. "
msgstr "The mind remains unaffected. It is steady, imperturbable, observing disappearance. "

# NOTE: I use feet rather than metres as the length is still approxiamately correct, and it retains the numerical symbolism.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.405, sc6
msgctxt "an9.26:6.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, silāyūpo soḷasakukkuko. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a stone pillar, sixteen feet long. "

msgctxt "an9.26:6.2"
msgid "Tassassu aṭṭha kukkū heṭṭhā nemaṅgamā, aṭṭha kukkū upari nemassa. "
msgstr "Eight feet were buried underground, and eight above ground. "

msgctxt "an9.26:6.3"
msgid "Atha puratthimāya cepi disāya āgaccheyya bhusā vātavuṭṭhi, neva naṃ saṅkampeyya na sampavedheyya; "
msgstr "And violent storms were to blow up out of the east, the west, the north, and the south. "

msgctxt "an9.26:6.4"
msgid "atha pacchimāya … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an9.26:6.5"
msgid "atha uttarāya … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an9.26:6.6"
msgid "atha dakkhiṇāya cepi disāya āgaccheyya bhusā vātavuṭṭhi, neva naṃ saṅkampeyya na sampavedheyya. "
msgstr "They couldn’t make it tremor and tremble and quake. "

msgctxt "an9.26:6.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an9.26:6.8"
msgid "Gambhīrattā, āvuso, nemassa, sunikhātattā silāyūpassa. "
msgstr "It’s because that boundary pillar is firmly embedded, with deep foundations. "

msgctxt "an9.26:6.9"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, sammā vimuttacittassa bhikkhuno bhusā cepi cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā cakkhussa āpāthaṃ āgacchanti, nevassa cittaṃ pariyādiyanti; "
msgstr "In the same way, when a mendicant’s mind is rightly freed like this, even if compelling sights come into the range of vision they don’t occupy their mind. "

msgctxt "an9.26:6.10"
msgid "amissīkatamevassa cittaṃ hoti ṭhitaṃ āneñjappattaṃ, vayaṃ cassānupassati. "
msgstr "The mind remains unaffected. It is steady, imperturbable, observing disappearance. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an9.26:7.1"
msgid "Bhusā cepi sotaviññeyyā saddā … "
msgstr "If even compelling sounds … "

msgctxt "an9.26:7.2"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyā gandhā … "
msgstr "smells … "

msgctxt "an9.26:7.3"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyā rasā … "
msgstr "tastes … "

msgctxt "an9.26:7.4"
msgid "kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā … "
msgstr "touches … "

msgctxt "an9.26:7.5"
msgid "manoviññeyyā dhammā manassa āpāthaṃ āgacchanti, nevassa cittaṃ pariyādiyanti; "
msgstr "and thoughts come into the range of the mind they don’t occupy the mind. "

msgctxt "an9.26:7.6"
msgid "amissīkatamevassa cittaṃ hoti ṭhitaṃ āneñjappattaṃ, vayaṃ cassānupassatī”ti. "
msgstr "The mind remains unaffected. It is steady, imperturbable, observing disappearance.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
